 at the origins of Jewish modernity. Hundert puts this experience, that of the majority of the Jewish people, at the center of his history. He focuses on the relations of Jews with the state and their role in the economy, and on more "internal" developments such as the popularization of the Kabbalah and the rise of Hasidism. Thus he describes the elements of Jewish experience that became the basis for a "core Jewish identity"-an identity that accompanied the majority of Jews into modernity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aHasidismzEurope, EasternxHistoryy18th century. 0aJewszLithuaniaxEconomic conditionsy18th century. 0aJewszLithuaniaxHistoryy18th century. 0aJewszLithuaniaxSocial conditionsy18th century. 0aJewszPolandxEconomic conditionsy18th century. 0aJewszPolandxHistoryy18th century. 0aJewszPolandxSocial conditionsy18th century. 0aMysticismxJudaismxHistoryy18th century. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520940321423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520940321.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles